==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Peart
<hw>Peart</hw> <pr>(p⟦emac⟧rt)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[A variant of
<ets>pert</ets>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <def>Active; lively; brisk; smart;
-- often applied to convalescents; <as>as, she is quite <ex>peart</ex>
to-day</as>.</def> <mark>[O. Eng. & Colloq. U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There was a tricksy girl, I wot, albeit clad in gray,⟦br⟧
As <qex>peart</qex> as bird, as straight as bolt, as fresh as flowers in
May.</q> <rj><qau>Warner (1592).</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Peasant</ent>⟦br⟧
